      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am not exactly sure I get this.  Do you have something like \"run_params(..., params: MinijailParams)\" where \"struct MinijailParams\" provides the parameters and the function is a super set of all other variants?\n\nI thought about that before, and felt we could follow https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/process/index.html and use a builder pattern.  But I am not super familiar with Rust to design a new set of APIs.  I would also hope to get this in sooner such that I can enable Mesa shader cache and get nice performance boost.",
